The Original Snow Village
Revised 10/29/2022

The Original Snow Village is the foundation upon which all village collections were inspired. The rudimentary snow house designs of 1976 gave birth to a collecting craze that has spanned through generations of families and across every socioeconomic boundary. Buildings are larger in size compared to those in The Heritage Village Collection and are made of ceramic. Its larger footprint and accessory scale varies throughout its history. Reflective of Main Street USA in the 1950s, it is the single largest collection of all village offerings.

The American Architecture Series, Brite Lites Parade, the over-decorated homes of Christmas Lane, Christmas Court trailer homes, Farmer's Market, as well as the ongoing Santa Comes To Town collection and Christmas On The Lake Fish Houses are just some of the subseries' that may be found in The Original Snow Village.

Department 56 and the Original Snow Village began with the release of six very distinct lit buildings in 1976. The craftsmanship of these early releases was not as polished as we have come to know. They were packaged in brown cardboard boxes with blue writing. The “village craze” truly began with these buildings and with their subsequent retirement in 1979. Coordinating Accessories were not designed until 1979.
